Name: philophthalmiasis
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of the eyes by Philophthalmus species. External ocular philophthalmiasis manifests as follicular conjunctivitis and superficial keratitis. Sub-conjunctival ocular philophthalmiasis consists of a mild edema with minimal cellular reaction.

Name: coenurosis
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves infection by metacestode larval stage (coenurus) of Taenia multiceps or Taenia serialis. Coenuri in the skin or subcutaneous tissue present as painless nodules

Name: obsolete Dipylidium caninum infectious disease
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection in dogs

Name: mesocestoidiasis
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic cestode infection caused by Mesocestoides lineatus resulting in nausea

Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection by the nematode Dioctophyme renale in humans after eating undercooked food. The larvae are found in the subcutaneous nodules and kidneys.

Name: obsolete tick paralysis

Name: taeniasis
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that has_material_basis_in Taenia solium or has_material_basis_in Taenia saginata

Name: hymenolepiasis
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves infection of the bowel by Hymenolepis nana or Hymenolepis diminuta. The symptoms include diarrhea

Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection caused by Diphyllobothrium latum through the consumption of raw or undercooked fish. The symptoms include abdominal discomfort

Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection due to migrating immature worms of Gnathostoma spinigerum or Gnathostoma hispidum

Name: fascioloidiasis

Name: enterobiasis
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves infection of the anus by the pinworm Enterobius vermicularis. The major symptom is perianal itching. Infected people experience perianal pruritus and excoriations from scratching.

Name: metagonimiasis
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of the intestine by Metagonimus yokogawai. The symptoms are diarrhea and colicky abdominal pain. The heart and brain can also be infected.

Name: obsolete tuberculous erythema nodosum
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of the intestine by Metagonimus yokogawai. The symptoms are diarrhea and colicky abdominal pain. The heart and brain can also be infected.

Name: obsolete Hodgkin's lymphoma
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of the intestine by Metagonimus yokogawai. The symptoms are diarrhea and colicky abdominal pain. The heart and brain can also be infected.
Synonym: nodular Sclerosis Hodgkin's Lymphoma stage III

Name: fasciolopsiasis

Name: monieziasis
